# Secure Vercel Deployment Plan & Tech Stack Documentation

This plan outlines deploying both the React Frontend and the Node/Express Backend on **Vercel** as two separate projects, keeping our secrets secure and ensuring smooth routing fallback for single-page app (SPA) URL paths.

---

## 1. Project Tech Stack

The application is built as a modern, premium MERN (MongoDB, Express, React, Node) stack project.

```mermaid
graph TD
    Client[React Frontend / Vite] -->|API Requests| Server[Node/Express Backend]
    Server -->|Mongoose ODM| DB[(MongoDB Atlas Cloud)]
    Client -->|Icons| Lucide[Lucide React Icons]
    Client -->|State Management| Zustand[Zustand Store]
    Server -->|Security & Auth| JWT[JWT / Cookies]
```

### Frontend (Client)
* **Core:** React 19, JavaScript (ES6+), Vite (Build Tool & Dev Server).
* **Styling:** Vanilla CSS & Tailwind CSS v3 (configured with theme variables matching system palettes).
* **State Management:** Zustand (lightweight, reactive global store).
* **Routing:** React Router DOM v7 (handles client-side routes like `/`, `/dashboard`, `/profile`).
* **Icons:** Lucide React.
* **Componentry & UX:** Glassmorphism UI cards, custom modal overlays, custom SVG analytic charts, and `react-hot-toast` notifications.

### Backend (Server)
* **Runtime:** Node.js, Express.js.
* **Database Access:** Mongoose ODM (Object Document Mapper).
* **Authentication:** JSON Web Tokens (JWT) for access validation, stored in-memory, paired with HTTP-Only secure Cookies for long-lived refresh tokens.
* **Validation:** Zod (schema validation for registrations, logins, and profile updates).
* **Rate Limiting:** Express Rate Limit (configured to protect authentications and general endpoints).

### Database (Data Store)
* **Provider:** MongoDB Atlas (fully-managed database cloud service).
* **Features:** Optimized compound single-field indexes for board queries and activity feeds.

