## 2. Deployment Architecture (All Vercel)

We will deploy the frontend and backend as **two separate Vercel projects** to manage separate environment variables, domains, and builds.

```mermaid
graph LR
    User((User)) -->|HTTPS| Frontend[Vercel Frontend Project <br/> Static Host]
    Frontend -->|HTTP-Only Cookie / CORS| Backend[Vercel Backend Project <br/> Serverless Functions]
    Backend -->|Auth Connection| MongoDB[(MongoDB Atlas)]
```

### Vercel Project Breakdown:
1. **`optimus-client` (Frontend):** Builds from the `client/` subdirectory. Configured to route all client subpaths to `index.html` (SPA mode).
2. **`optimus-server` (Backend):** Builds from the `server/` subdirectory using Vercel's Node.js Serverless runtime (`@vercel/node`).

