## 3. Proposed Changes

### 1. Server Configuration (Vercel Serverless Setup)

#### [MODIFY] [server/src/app.js](file:///c:/Users/Grim%20Reaper/Desktop/OptimusAutomate_PMTool/server/src/app.js)
* Export `app` so Vercel can load the Express listener.
* Prevent starting the local listener using `app.listen()` when running inside Vercel's serverless environment (checking `process.env.VERCEL`):
  ```javascript
  const PORT = process.env.PORT || 5000;
  if (process.env.VERCEL !== '1') {
    app.listen(PORT, () => {
      console.log(`✅ Server running in ${process.env.NODE_ENV || 'development'} mode on port ${PORT}`);
    });
  }

  export default app;
  ```

#### [NEW] [server/vercel.json](file:///c:/Users/Grim%20Reaper/Desktop/OptimusAutomate_PMTool/server/vercel.json)
* Define the build configuration to route all incoming backend requests to the Express entry point `src/app.js` using `@vercel/node`:
  ```json
  {
    "version": 2,
    "builds": [
      {
        "src": "src/app.js",
        "use": "@vercel/node"
      }
    ],
    "routes": [
      {
        "src": "/(.*)",
        "dest": "src/app.js"
      }
    ]
  }
  ```

---

### 2. Client Configuration (Vercel Routing Rules)

#### [NEW] [client/vercel.json](file:///c:/Users/Grim%20Reaper/Desktop/OptimusAutomate_PMTool/client/vercel.json)
* Add SPA route rewrites to prevent `404 Not Found` errors when refreshing pages like `/dashboard` or `/profile`:
  ```json
  {
    "cleanUrls": true,
    "rewrites": [
      {
        "source": "/(.*)",
        "destination": "/index.html"
      }
    ]
  }
  ```

