## 4. Cloud Deployment Setup Steps

### 1. Backend Deployment (on Vercel)
* Go to the Vercel dashboard and click **Import Project**.
* Select the repository, set the project name to your backend's name.
* In **Root Directory**, select the `server` folder.
* Configure **Environment Variables** in Vercel settings:
  * `NODE_ENV=production`
  * `MONGO_URI` (your MongoDB Atlas connection string)
  * `JWT_SECRET` (secure random string)
  * `JWT_REFRESH_SECRET` (secure random string)
  * `CLIENT_URL` (the live Vercel URL of your deployed frontend)

### 2. Frontend Deployment (on Vercel)
* Import the repository again as a separate project.
* Set the project name to your client's name.
* In **Root Directory**, select the `client` folder.
* Verify Vercel automatically detects the Vite framework.
* Configure **Environment Variables**:
  * `VITE_API_URL` (pointing to your deployed backend URL, e.g. `https://your-backend-vercel.app/api`)

